<subSubSection id="B4F06548B11CA13CEBADFDB4E25BFD27" pageId="16" pageNumber="467" type="distribution">
<paragraph id="FC5536C3B11CA13CEBADFDB4E25BFD27" blockId="16.[151,1436,613,818]" pageId="16" pageNumber="467">
<emphasis id="CE9EEAD1B11CA13CEBADFDB4E15AFDFB" bold="true" box="[151,304,613,638]" pageId="16" pageNumber="467">Distribution.</emphasis>
Restricted to the fynbos habitats in Hawequa Mountains of the southwestern Western Cape Province, 
<collectingCountry id="84FD7653B11CA13CEBADFD58E14DFD27" box="[151,295,649,674]" name="South Africa" pageId="16" pageNumber="467">South Africa</collectingCountry>
(
<bibRefCitation id="987B4B32B11CA13CEA0FFD5BE1ADFD27" author="Bauer" box="[309,455,650,674]" pageId="16" pageNumber="467" refString="Bauer, A. M. (2014 c) Afroedura hawequensis Mouton &amp; Mostert, 1985. In: Bates, M. F., Branch, W. R., Bauer, A. M., Burger, M., Marais, J., Alexander, G. J. &amp; de Villiers, M. (Eds.), Atlas and Red List of the Reptiles of South Africa, Lesotho and Swaziland. Suricata, 1. South African National Biodiversity Institute, Pretoria, pp. 92 - 93." type="journal article" year="2014" yearSuffix="c">
Bauer 
<number id="4A2224E4B11CA13CEABBFD5BE1D1FD27" box="[385,443,650,674]" pageId="16" pageNumber="467" value="2014.0">2014</number>
c
</bibRefCitation>
) (
<figureCitation id="64D12A46B11CA13CEAE4FD58E249FD27" box="[478,547,649,674]" captionStart="FIGURE 4" captionStartId="18.[151,250,1165,1187]" captionTargetBox="[181,1379,205,1164]" captionTargetId="figure@18.[172,1393,177,1165]" captionTargetPageId="18" captionText="FIGURE 4. Map of southern Africa showing the approximate distributional ranges of previously described species of Afroedura. Red dots represent localities sampled for the genetic portion of the study. Ranges based on Branch (1998) and Bates et al. (2014) as well as unpublished data. Taxon names follow the conclusions of this paper. Area demarcated by a dashed line is presented in more detail in Figure 6." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/250499/files/figure.png" pageId="16" pageNumber="467">
Fig. 
<number id="4A2224E4B11CA13CE928FD5BE249FD27" box="[530,547,650,674]" pageId="16" pageNumber="467" value="4.0">4</number>
</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="B4F06548B11CA13CEBFDFD7CE155FCB7" pageId="16" pageNumber="467" type="discussion">
<paragraph id="FC5536C3B11CA13CEBFDFD7CE155FCB7" blockId="16.[151,1436,613,818]" pageId="16" pageNumber="467">
<emphasis id="CE9EEAD1B11CA13CEBFDFD7CE151FD43" bold="true" box="[199,315,685,710]" pageId="16" pageNumber="467">Remarks.</emphasis>
This species is the sister to all remaining congeners. It was previously considered a member of the 
<taxonomicName id="3BEA4D40B11CA13CEBADFD03E17EFD6F" box="[151,276,722,746]" class="Reptilia" family="Gekkonidae" genus="Afroedura" kingdom="Animalia" order="Squamata" pageId="16" pageNumber="467" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="africana">
<emphasis id="CE9EEAD1B11CA13CEBADFD03E17EFD6F" box="[151,276,722,746]" italics="true" pageId="16" pageNumber="467">A. africana</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
group (
<bibRefCitation id="987B4B32B11CA13CEA50FD03E2EAFD6F" author="Mouton" box="[362,640,721,746]" pageId="16" pageNumber="467" refString="Mouton, P. le F. N. &amp; Mostert, D. P. (1985) Description of a new species of Afroedura (Loveridge) (Reptilia: Gekkonidae) from the south - western Cape. South African Journal of Zoology, 20, 246 - 249." type="journal article" year="1985">
Mouton &amp; Mostert 
<number id="4A2224E4B11CA13CE97EFD00E2EAFD6F" box="[580,640,721,746]" pageId="16" pageNumber="467" value="1985.0">1985</number>
</bibRefCitation>
). The species was previously listed in the 
<emphasis id="CE9EEAD1B11CA13CEF68FD00E5F6FD6F" box="[1106,1436,721,746]" italics="true" pageId="16" pageNumber="467">South African Red Data Book</emphasis>
as “Restricted” (
<bibRefCitation id="987B4B32B11CA13CEA6EFD27E19BFC8B" author="Mouton" box="[340,497,758,782]" pageId="16" pageNumber="467" refString="Mouton, P. le F. N. (1988) Afroedura hawequensis. In: Branch, W. R. (Ed.), South African Red Data Book - Reptiles and Amphibians. South African National Scientific Programmes Report No. 151. CSIR, Pretoria, pp. 139 - 140." type="book chapter" year="1988">
Mouton 
<number id="4A2224E4B11CA13CEA82FD27E19BFC8B" box="[440,497,758,782]" pageId="16" pageNumber="467" value="1988.0">1988</number>
</bibRefCitation>
) and is currently considered as Near Threatened under 
<collectionCode id="9AFBAE06B11CA13CEF42FD27E4D6FC8B" box="[1144,1212,758,782]" pageId="16" pageNumber="467">IUCN</collectionCode>
assessment criteria (
<bibRefCitation id="987B4B32B11CA13CEBA4FCCBE159FCB7" author="Bauer" box="[158,307,794,818]" pageId="16" pageNumber="467" refString="Bauer, A. M. (2014 c) Afroedura hawequensis Mouton &amp; Mostert, 1985. In: Bates, M. F., Branch, W. R., Bauer, A. M., Burger, M., Marais, J., Alexander, G. J. &amp; de Villiers, M. (Eds.), Atlas and Red List of the Reptiles of South Africa, Lesotho and Swaziland. Suricata, 1. South African National Biodiversity Institute, Pretoria, pp. 92 - 93." type="journal article" year="2014" yearSuffix="c">
Bauer 
<number id="4A2224E4B11CA13CEBD0FCCBE14DFCB7" box="[234,295,794,818]" pageId="16" pageNumber="467" value="2014.0">2014</number>
c
</bibRefCitation>
).
</paragraph>
